		 'm'  Remap keys. This is default.  If {mode} is absent,
		   keys are remapped.
		 'n'  Do not remap keys.
		 't'  Handle keys as if typed; otherwise they are handled as
		   if coming from a mapping.  This matters for undo,
		   opening folds, etc.
